### **Docker - Hinglish mein bahut simple**

**Docker** ek tool hai jo **hamari application ko uski saari dependencies ke saath ek box (container) mein pack kar deta hai.**

### Example

Maan lo tumne apni **Spring Boot application** apne laptop par banayi.

* Tumhare laptop par **Java 17** hai, isliye application chal rahi hai.
* Server par **Java 11** hai, to application nahi chalegi. ❌

**Docker kya karta hai?**

Wo application + Java + saari required libraries ko **ek container** mein pack kar deta hai.

Ab wahi container:

* ✅ Laptop par chalega
* ✅ Dev server par chalega
* ✅ Production server par bhi same chalega

### Easy analogy 📦

**Docker Container = Tiffin Box**

* 🍛 Food = Application
* 📦 Tiffin Box = Docker Container

Jahan bhi tiffin le jaoge, andar ka food same rahega.

Waise hi, **jahan bhi Docker container run karoge, application same tarike se chalegi.**

### Interview answer (20 sec)

> **Docker ka use application aur uski saari dependencies ko ek container mein pack karne ke liye hota hai, taaki application har environment (Developer, Testing, Production) mein bina kisi issue ke same tarike se chale.**

**One-line yaad rakhna:**

> **Docker = "Package once, run anywhere."** 📦


