# Only 8-10 topics are left

If you learn these, your Docker preparation will be around **95-98% complete**.

---

## 1. What is a Volume?

Very commonly asked.

Simple answer:

> **Volume is used to store data permanently. Even if the container is deleted, the data remains safe.**

Example

Database data

Logs

Uploaded files

---

## 2. Difference between COPY and ADD

Very common.

```
COPY
Only copies files.

ADD
Copies files + can extract tar files + download from URL.
```

Interview answer

> **Mostly we use COPY. ADD has some additional features.**

---

## 3. Difference between CMD and ENTRYPOINT

Very common.

Simple answer

```
ENTRYPOINT

Fixed command.

CMD

Default command.
Can be overridden.
```

---

## 4. Docker Logs

Command

```bash
docker logs container-name
```

Meaning

See application logs.

Interviewer may ask

How do you debug Docker issues?

Answer

> **I check the container logs using `docker logs`.**

---

## 5. Docker Exec

Command

```bash
docker exec -it container-name bash
```

Meaning

Go inside the running container.

Example

Need to check

```
Files

Logs

Java Version

Configurations
```

---

## 6. Difference between docker stop and docker rm

Very common.

```
docker stop

Stops container.

docker rm

Deletes container.
```

---

## 7. Docker Images command

```
docker images
```

Shows all images.

---

## 8. Docker Pull

```
docker pull openjdk:17
```

Downloads image from Docker Hub.

---

## 9. Port Mapping

Very very common.

Command

```bash
docker run -p 8080:8080 user-service
```

Meaning

```
Laptop Port 8080

↓

Container Port 8080
```

Sometimes interviewer asks

> Why -p?

Answer

> **It maps the host machine port to the container port so that we can access the application from outside the container.**

---

## 10. Real Project Flow (Most Important)

Many interviewers ask

> Explain how Docker is used in your project.

Answer

```
Developer writes Spring Boot code
        │
        ▼
Build JAR using Maven
        │
        ▼
Write Dockerfile
        │
        ▼
docker build
        │
        ▼
Docker Image
        │
        ▼
Push Image to Docker Hub
        │
        ▼
Dev Server pulls Image
        │
        ▼
docker run
        │
        ▼
Docker Container
        │
        ▼
Application Running
        │
        ▼
Test APIs using Postman
```

This single flow answers **4-5 interview questions**.

